{"id": "codex-20260513-162913-b07fzqxxxxxx", "agent": "codex", "description": "# Plan: Harness Standardization & aq-memory Implementation (Slice 33.1)\n\n## Objective\nStabilize the AI harness execution environment by standardizing configuration via environment variables, clearing the current task backlog using a reliable remote LLM, and implementing the `aq-memory` CLI tool as the first step in the TokenMaxxing framework.\n\n## Key Files & Context\n- `/var/lib/nixos-ai-stack/optimizer/overrides.env`: Persistent configuration.\n- `ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/workflow/workflow_executor.py`: Executor logic.\n- `ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/core/llm_client.py`: LLM client logic.\n- `scripts/ai/aq-memory`: The new memory management script.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Persistent Environment Configuration\nUpdate `/var/lib/nixos-ai-stack/optimizer/overrides.env` to permanently store the working OpenRouter configuration. This replaces the ad-hoc shell variables used during troubleshooting.\n*   `WORKFLOW_EXECUTOR_PROVIDER=anthropic`\n*   `WORKFLOW_EXECUTOR_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api`\n*   `WORKFLOW_EXECUTOR_MODEL=google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite:free`\n*   Ensure the script sources the API key securely (e.g., mapping `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` to the value read from `/run/secrets/remote_llm_api_key`).\n\n### Step 2: Codebase Standardization Validation\nEnsure the recent \"hack\" fixes made to `workflow_executor.py` and `llm_client.py` during the diagnostic phase are clean, robust, and follow the project's coding standards. They must cleanly accept the environment overrides established in Step 1.\n\n### Step 3: Reliable Background Execution\nStart the `workflow_executor.py` using `nohup` or a similar daemonizing approach so that it persistently processes the `workflow-sessions.json` queue without crashing on terminal disconnects.\n\n### Step 4: Implement `aq-memory` CLI\nCreate the `scripts/ai/aq-memory` executable script. This fulfills Task #1 in the executor queue.\n*   **Purpose**: Allow agents to store and recall structured memory context.\n*   **Input**: Key-value pairs or text chunks.\n*   **Output**: Compressed references or targeted retrieval (aligning with TokenMaxxing goals to reduce context waste).\n\n## Verification & Testing\n1.  Verify the `overrides.env` file contains the correct structure.\n2.  Check `/tmp/workflow-executor.log` to confirm the 7 queued sessions are successfully processed without 401 or 503 errors.\n3.  Run `scripts/ai/aq-memory --help` to ensure the new script is executable and syntactically correct.", "output_file": ".agents/delegation/outputs/codex-20260513-162913-b07fzqxxxxxx.log", "pid": null, "status": "running", "created": "2026-05-13T23:29:13Z"}
